# Embedded Systems C/Assembly Code Rules

## Code Style
- Use K&R brace style for C code.
- Use 4-space indentation with no tabs.
- Keep lines to a maximum of 100 characters.
- Prefix static functions with an underscore.
- Use explicit fixed-width types (for example, `uint32_t` instead of `int`).
- Add Doxygen comments for all public functions.

## Embedded Best Practices
- Never use `malloc`/`free` in ISRs.
- Use `volatile` for hardware registers and shared variables.
- Use `const` for lookup tables stored in flash.
- Use types from `stdint.h` and `stdbool.h`.
- Check all pointer dereferences.
- Initialize all variables.
- Do not use recursion (stack overflow risk).
- Do not use VLAs (variable length arrays).

## ARM Cortex-M Specific
- Align stack to 8-byte boundaries.
- Use CMSIS standards where applicable.
- Document interrupt priority levels.
- Clear pending interrupts before enabling.
- Use `__attribute__((section))` for linker placement.

## Documentation
- Include `README.md` in each directory.
- Keep architecture diagrams in `docs/`.
- Write comments that explain why, not what.
- Document all assumptions.
